# Title: Potential Abuse of Linux Magic System Request Key
# Author: Milad Cheraghi
# Date: 2025-05-23
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects the potential abuse of the Linux Magic SysRq (System Request) key by adversaries with root or sufficient privileges
# to silently manipulate or destabilize a system. By writing to /proc/sysrq-trigger, they can crash the system, kill processes,
# or disrupt forensic analysisâ€”all while bypassing standard logging. Though intended for recovery and debugging, SysRq can be
# misused as a stealthy post-exploitation tool. It is controlled via /proc/sys/kernel/sysrq or permanently through /etc/sysctl.conf.
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution, attack.t1059.004, attack.impact, attack.t1529, attack.t1489, attack.t1499
# False Positives:
#   - Legitimate administrative activity

name IN ("*/sysrq", "*/sysctl.conf", "*/sysrq-trigger") type="PATH"